# UI Templ Documentation Rule

When working in `ui/**/*`, treat `docs/templ.md` as the primary reference for templ syntax, component patterns, and rendering behavior.

## Required workflow

- Follow templ patterns from `docs/templ.md` before introducing new template constructs.
- Keep markup/components in `*.templ` and styles in matching `*.styles.templ` files.
- Never manually edit generated `*_templ.go` files.
- After changing any `*.templ` file, run `templ generate` and include generated updates.
- Use regular Go view models/prepared data instead of complex data shaping directly in templates.

## Guardrails

- Avoid code-only HTML rendering unless necessary; if used, escape content correctly.
- Keep template logic readable: prefer simple `if`, `switch`, and `for`, and move heavy logic to Go code.
- If uncertain about templ behavior, check `docs/templ.md` first and follow its documented approach.

## Examples

```text
Good: edit ui/features/host_actions/host_actions.templ, run templ generate, commit both source and generated files.
Bad: edit ui/features/host_actions/host_actions_templ.go directly to "quick fix" output.
```
